						<summary>

						<p>On the west wall, central shrine, Sākshīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 13: 984 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 2 <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> and a <hi rend="italic">kāṇi</hi> of land in Vānavanmādēvi-chaturvēdimaṅgalam in Innambar-nāḍu on the northern bank of the river (Kāvēri) for burning 1(1/2) perpetual lamps with 1(1/2) <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of oil, in the temple of Āditta-Īśvaram-uḍaiyār at Tiruppuṟambiyam, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> separated from Aṇḍāṭṭu-kūṟṟam, by Śeṭṭi Perumāṉ of Maṇaṟkuḍi in Maṇaṟkuḍi-nāḍu also on the northern bank.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 328.</p>						

						</summary>
